Call `find_package()` conditionally.

If a top-level project has called `add_directory(abseil-cpp)` already (possibly
indirectly), let that take precedence over any copy of Abseil that might have
been installed on the system. And likewise for ICU, GoogleTest and Benchmark.

Fixes #427.

Use `--enable_platform_specific_config` in `.bazelrc`.

This magically applies the `linux`, `macos` or `windows` configuration
depending on the OS. Apart from simplifying things for us, this should
hopefully also unbreak the RE2 build that Bazel folks run in their CI.

Fixes #428.
